ems#Anti-Patterns#❌ Store Everything Forever":[47,48],"#Agent Memory Systems#Anti-Patterns#❌ Chunk Without Testing Retrieval":[49,50],"#Agent Memory Systems#Anti-Patterns#❌ Single Memory Type for All Data":[51,52],"#Agent Memory Systems#⚠️ Sharp Edges":[53,64],"#Agent Memory Systems#⚠️ Sharp Edges#{1}":[55,64],"#Agent Memory Systems#Related Skills":[65,68],"#Agent Memory Systems#Related Skills#{1}":[67,68]},"outlinks":[],"metadata":{"name":"agent-memory-systems","description":"Memory is the cornerstone of intelligent agents. Without it, every interaction starts from zero. This skill covers the architecture of agent memory: short-term (context window), long-term (vector stores), and the cognitive architectures that organize them.  Key insight: Memory isn't just storage - it's retrieval. A million stored facts mean nothing if you can't find the right one. Chunking, embedding, and retrieval strategies determine whether your agent remembers or forgets.  The field is fragm","source":"vibeship-spawner-skills (Apache 2.0)"},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"key":"00_System/Links/App_agent_skills_repo/agent-memory-systems/SKILL.md"},
